<paragraph blockId="13.[131,777,304,1312]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName box="[132,276,304,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Adansonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="twining" subSpecies="herb">A twining herb</taxonomicName>
with ovate, coriacous and discolorous leaves indistinguishable from
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[280,407,330,354]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Marsdenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigriflora">M. nigriflora</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">by vegetative characters, but otherwise unique within New Caledonian</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[443,547,357,381]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Marsdenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Marsdenia</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
species because of its radiate flowers of around 
<quantity box="[351,420,384,408]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
diam. with adaxially glabrous corolla lobes, bipartite staminal corona lobes differentiated into a swollen, transversally ovate base and a lingulate apical part. The style-head is subconical and slightly papillate, and thus very similar to the one of
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[133,259,489,513]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Marsdenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigriflora">M. nigriflora</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
