<paragraph blockId="13.[131,777,304,1312]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3113722343" collectionCode="IUCN, CR" collectorName="de Ho" location="Ho region" municipality="Houailou. The" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" specimenCode="B1" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Province Nord">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — So far, the only known locality of this new species is at Hô, just north of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[464,607,944,968]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Houaïlou. The</collectingMunicipality>
col 
<collectorName box="[647,707,944,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
de 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A287B7FFBDFFDF768EFF2FFE8FFA45:8ED4607AFFBDFFDF74C5FC49FD2CFC21" box="[675,707,945,969]" municipality="Houailou. The" name="Ho region" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" stateProvince="Province Nord">Hô</location>
</collectorName>
region and the Cap Bocage peninsula are renowned for several rare species despite a general lack of botanical knowledge for the area. As a whole this region could be considered as an “ultramafic island”. Most of the area is under nickel mining concession and the Cap Bocage peninsula is under active mining. The other main threat in this region are the severe bush fires that frequently occur. The 
<collectingRegion box="[133,285,1129,1153]" country="New Caledonia" name="Province Nord" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">North Province</collectingRegion>
“Nature Guard” Philippe Nekotrotro has recently surveyed the 
<typeStatus box="[255,296,1156,1180]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">type</typeStatus>
locality for this species without success. Considering that the remnants of rainforest pockets in the area are under fire and mining pressure, 
<taxonomicName authority="Liede" authorityName="Liede" authorityYear="2017" box="[340,571,1209,1233]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Marsdenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="weberlingiana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[340,507,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">M. weberlingiana</emphasis>
Liede
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[580,654,1209,1232]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is assigned a preliminary 
<collectionCode box="[252,317,1235,1259]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">IUCN</collectionCode>
conservation status of “Critically endangered” [
<collectionCode box="[138,174,1262,1286]" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
<specimenCode box="[181,206,1262,1286]" collectionCode="B" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" type="Herbarium">B1</specimenCode>
ab(i,ii,iii,v)+2ab(i,ii,iii,v)] using Red List criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10534" refString="IUCN 2012. - IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1 Second edition. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge." type="book" year="2012">IUCN, 2012</bibRefCitation>
) if not Extinct
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
